<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;">Naval officers and others need not hesitate to use lethal force against pirates: </span>**__The U__**<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;">nited </span>**__N__**<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;">ations </span>**__Security Council passed resolution 1851__**<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;"> in December 2008 </span>**__authorizing states to take "all necessary measures__**<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;">—that are appropriate in Somalia, </span>**__for the purpose of suppressing__**<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;"> acts of </span>**__piracy." This__**<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;"> was issued under Chapter VII of the U.N. Charter and </span>**__should serve as a sufficient legal basis to kill pirates.__**<span style="color: #a6a6a6; font-size: 6pt;"> Further, the law of self-defense ought to cover the use of lethal force against pirates boarding ships armed with lethal weapons. </span>


